{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-situations-page-tsx","path":"/en/situations/churches-and-religious-activities/funerals","result":{"data":{"situation":{"title":"Funerals","meta_description":"Rules and recommendations for funerals","content":{"processed":"<h2>Rules and recommendations</h2>\n<p>\nFunerals are allowed <strong>but only 30 people can be present</strong>. The general obligations to wear a mask and follow hygienic regulations apply. As part of preventive measures, it's obligatory to keep social distance (even when sitting).</p>\n<p>The wake <strong>can be held in a restaurant</strong> or other catering facilities. For the wake, a limit of <strong>30 people present applies. </strong>Restaurants must follow specific hygiene rules.</p>\n<p>Alternatively, you can meet your relatives and friends you would have met at the funeral/wake <strong>at home</strong>. Please follow the hygienic regulations, even when consuming food or drink.</p>\n<p>Funeral homes are allowed to operate, the exemption from the ban on the provision of services applies specifically to funeral services (embalming, conservation, cremation of human remains or ashes and placing human ashes in urns).</p>\n"},"path":{"alias":"/situations/churches-and-religious-activities/funerals"},"changed":"2020-12-14T22:58:16+00:00","valid_from":null,"langcode":"en","created":"2020-11-09T21:47:01+00:00","links":[],"relationships":{"region":[{"name":"All regions of Czechia"}],"icon":null,"situation_type":{"name":"Churches and religious activities","path":{"alias":"/situations/churches-and-religious-activities"},"relationships":{"icon":{"code":"account_balance"}}},"measures":[],"related_situations":[{"title":"Grief and loss","path":{"alias":"/situations/stress-and-handling-impacts-pandemic/grief-and-loss","langcode":"en"}},{"title":"Confessions and individual spiritual care ","path":{"alias":"/situations/churches-and-religious-activities/confessions-and-individual-spiritual-care","langcode":"en"